<div id="review_2196504214" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2196504214" />
    <a title="coolwind" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27601004-coolwind"><img alt="coolwind" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486558465p2/27601004.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2196504214?book_show_action=true">Dec 01, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="coolwind" class="user" itemprop="url" name="coolwind" href="/user/show/27601004-coolwind">coolwind</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2196504214" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15988538092138422656">To understand America and its modern political environment, I think one has to understand the revolution and civil war. This is the first book of trilogy. It gives a vivid account of escalations of the national tension on slavery and later turned to union problems. It is unprepared and unforeseen by everyone. Yet it moved to the direction of unavoidable. The coming fury. <br/><br/>This is a history book. But the author’s writing style and language used is fantastic.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


