<div id="review_3931585736" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3931585736" />
    <a title="Patrick Kelley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/815254-patrick-kelley"><img alt="Patrick Kelley" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3931585736?book_show_action=true">Apr 07, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patrick Kelley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patrick Kelley" href="/user/show/815254-patrick-kelley">Patrick Kelley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3931585736" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8204298483265284285">Bruce Catton’s books on the Civil War are among the best that have been written. This book is thoroughly researched, written simply but provides incredible depth to understanding the conflict. It’s greatest achievement is how much of the book can be applied to our current political divides. What makes this book somewhat unique to the literature of the Civil War is that it has a Northerner’s perspective. This book should be read by all.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


